-ablution\/","url_meta":{"origin":13895,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: When the Prophet forgot ablution for prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 22, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The prayer had been prepared and the rows straightened, then the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, came out to us. When he stood in his place of prayer, he remembered that he was in a state of ritual impurity (junub). The Prophet said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15926,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/05\/angels-bless-remain-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":13895,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Masjid: Angels bless those who wait for prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe prayer of a man in congregation is twenty-five times better than prayer in his home or shop. When he performs ablution in a good manner and leaves to the mosque only to perform the prayer,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32976,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/forgives-between-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":13895,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Allah forgives what one did between prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA Muslim man does not perform ablution in an excellent manner and then performs prayer, but that Allah will forgive him for what occurred between his prayer and the next.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 158, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34732,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/21\/prophet-asks-nur-noor\/","url_meta":{"origin":13895,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet asks Allah for light in his heart","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: He spent the night with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he woke up. The Prophet cleansed his teeth, performed ablution, the call to prayer was announced, and he went out for the prayer while he was saying, \u201cO Allah, place light\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":9733,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/11\/09\/qiblah-woman-salat-dogs\/","url_meta":{"origin":13895,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Does a woman invalidate a man&#8217;s prayer?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 9, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: That which invalidates prayer was mentioned in her presence and they said, \u201cPrayer is invalidated by a dog, a donkey, and a woman.\u201d Aisha said, \u201cYou have turned us into dogs! I have seen the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, praying while I was between him\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13895","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=13895"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13895\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=13895"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=13895"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=13895"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}